28/08/2003
ROUSSE, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria and Romania are working to strengthen security along their common border, according to the respective heads of border police, Valeri Grigorov and Aurel Neagu. 
At their regular meeting Wednesday (27 August), they agreed to begin patrols equipped with thermal vision equipment as of 1 October. 
(BNT, BTA - 27/08/03)
